<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: clerics and pvpers???</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Joruus Darevitam">Joruus Darevitam</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 5:57 p.m. 5/8/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: clerics and pvpers???<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2315" TARGET=_self>Re: clerics and pvpers???</A> (Ice)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> Clerics are a well balanced pvp class. They can defeat almost

<BR>&gt; all classes in a duel on even terms. It would be a good idea to
<BR>&gt; be one. As for race i would definetely go dwarf they just got
<BR>&gt; awesome stats. In addition, they will have control of unrest
<BR>&gt; which is a clerics favorite.
<BR>Clerics ROCK in pvp. I have a level 27th cleric. Clerics get one of the best pvp spells, flash of light (blindness) and cure disease (cure virtually any DoT spell) and cure blindness at the first or second spell circle. Clerics get fairly decent nuke spells and root. Clerics can wear all armor and wield all blunt weapons. A cleric can heal himself in a duel and can greatly extend his life. When i was level 14 i fought a level 15 necromancer (he wasn't using his pet). He dot'd me and drained all his mana messing me up. He got me down to about 3 bubbles then he ran out of mana. I healed myself once and i was back at full, and still had about 4 bubbles of mana left. I got in to close quarters and casted my DD spell and beat on him with my weapon and easily won the battle. Clerics are GREAT in group pvp situations as they can heal other members and greatly extend someone's life. One warning though: clerics will be one of if not the FIRST target in a group vs group pvp battle with maybe only wizards coming before them.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
